    "name": "The Mighty Ibex",
    "profile": "Born from the ashes of Angry Feet and Static Action, The Mighty Ibex created a bit of a racket with music that is confusing and catchy in equal measure. Take the Queens of the Stone Age discography, put it in a blender, blend for 4 and a half minutes until the contents resemble Russian Circles, At The Drive-In or early Biffy Clyro and you have The Mighty Ibex. The Liverpudlian band broke up in 2015.\r\n\r\nEdoardo Vittori (Drums)\r\nCharlie Gibbons (Bass)\r\nChris Catteral (Guitar)\r\nAsher Kenton (Guitar + Vox)",
